Hi, I’m a new programming coach for team 1555, and I’m having trouble installing the navx libraries into vs code. I tried using the online and offline installer methods, but neither way seemed to work. Java | navX-MXP This is the installation page, and I don’t know if the navx mxp is supported for 2023, but any help would be greatly appreciated.

open vs code, click control+shift+p, find “manage vendor libraries”,

image726×71 2.39 KB

select “Install new libraries (online)” and insert this link https://dev.studica.com/releases/2023/NavX.json
they don’t have an offline installation for their 2023 library as far as I know, so this is the way to do it
